\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844\charrsid1315844 Succeeded by a committee: Raphael, Denis Butt, Norman Fruchter, Frances Kelly. Raphael decided to switch th
e thematic issues, first on housing. But this was late, and three times as long.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844\charrsid1315844 Board then approached Perry Anderson. Perry was a bit younger, one of next Left generation with Mike Rustin, Robin Blackburn, Alan Shuttleworth. Perry Etonian, clever, scholar
ly, highly intellectual, uses many rare words. Immediately he started it became clear he had a different project. Unlike the amalgam which made up the New Left, not interested in British politics, but fascinated by Russian, German and French socialism. He
 
learnt Russian in military service. Board became restive. Edward wrote a critical letter which Perry refused to publish; most of old members left the Board. Journal continues at a high level, along with Verso publications, introducing Lukacs, Gramsci, mak
ing European Marxism available to British readers.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844 
