\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844\charrsid1315844 Kept in touch with Jamaican culture through music, visits and especially through the diaspora. Knew more Jamaicans in Birmingham than in London. Then at political meetings every
 other weekend.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844\charrsid1315844 
Never calls himself an academic, although that is where he worked and made many friends. Ambition was to be an intellectual. Did not care which discipline: anyway, when left Birmingham there were no other cultural studies departments.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid1315844 
